The two winners of @inifdcorporate presents #GenNext, @lineoutline.in by Deepit Chugh and @twinklehanspal have created two modern yet versatile collections at FDCI x Lakmé Fashion Week.

Line Outline by Deepit Chugh's latest showcase, 'Chapter 2- Idyll'  takes its visual inspiration from coloured brutalist architecture. Enveloped in soft cottons, cotton blends, bemberg silks and twill fabrics, it boasts of minimalistic hand embroideries like cording, pitta work and zardosi along with a focus on colour block and pattern play.

Twinkle Hanspal's collection is created with the modern union of East meets West where she celebrates the classic Indian silhouettes with a contemporary twist. Her latest showcase features a subtle palette that seamlessly translate into an array of colorblocked classics.
